I HAVE many times asked myself, not without wonder, the source of a certain
error which which, since it is committed by all the old without exception,
can be believe to be proper and natural to man: namely, that they nearly all
praise the past and blame the present, revile our actions and behaviour and
everything which they themselves did not do when they were young, and affirm,
too, that every good custom and way of life, every virtue and, in short, all
things imaginable are always going from bad to worse. And truly it seems...
TRANSLATION:
Don't trust anyone over 30...Baldesar Castiglione
Book II, The Book of the Courtier

